topic.title: Dynamic Port Bifurcation Command

body.p: The Dynamic Port Bifurcation Command is used to dynamically set the bifurcation of the unbound physical port.

li.p: Dynamic Bifurcation applies to DSP ports only. USP ports cannot be dynamically bifurcated.
(For more information on binding and unbinding physical ports, see Dynamic Partitioning .)

table.title: MRPC Dynamic Bifurcation Command Input Data

body.p:
The Sub-Command codes include:
0x0 - Get Stack Bifurcation
0x1 - Set Stack Bifurcation
All others reserved
These arguments change depending on the sub command, as shown in the table below.

section.title: Dynamic Port Bifurcation—Get Stack Bifurcation Sub-Command
section.p: The Get Stack Bifurcation Sub- Command is used to get the bifurcation information of a stack.

section.p: The bifurcation code is UINT32. Each four bits are used to specify ports in the stack.
The valid value for each port in the stack. For more information, see the table below.

table.title: Stack Bifurcation Code and Valid Port IDs

section.note: The Port ID mentioned here is different than the Physical Port ID which can uniquely identify the port. The Port ID here refers to ports in the same stack. For example, 0 means the 1st physical port in the stack; 4 means the 5th physical port in the stack.
section.p: Bifurcation code example: 0x11020004 gets/sets the 1st port to x8, 5th port to x4, 7th port to x2 and 8th port to x2. The other ports are disabled.

section.title: Dynamic Port Bifurcation—Set Stack Bifurcation Sub-Command
section.p: The Set Stack Bifurcation Sub-Command is used to set the bifurcation to a stack.
